<div class="about-body">
  <p>
    Hi, I'm Shane. I'm a data strategy and GTM engineer at
    <a href="https://www.verkada.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Verkada</a>,
    where I work on the Global Revenue Informatics team — building tooling,
    standardizing data at scale, and partnering with sales and marketing to
    sharpen how the company goes to market.
  </p>
  <p>
    Before Verkada, I spent two years as a business analyst at McKinsey &amp; Company,
    working across strategy, analytics, and client delivery. Before that, I studied
    economics and computer science at Vanderbilt University.
  </p>
  <p>
    On the technical side, I'm drawn to systems programming, language interpreters,
    and data infrastructure. I've worked through 80+ Project Euler problems (top 2%
    of solvers), which has given me a real appreciation for combinatorics and
    discrete math. I also care about social justice, institutional reform, and how
    technology shapes the way power and information flow.
  </p>
